                    "answer": "An Uninterruptible Power Supply (UPS) is designed for short-duration backup (minutes to hours) of sensitive electronics. Solar batteries are designed for whole-home or partial-home backup over hours to days. Solar batteries also integrate with your solar panels for daily energy management, while a UPS simply provides emergency power from a pre-charged internal battery."
