                    "answer": "Both work fine. However, DC Coupled systems often have \"Black Start\" capabilities built-in more naturally. AC Coupled systems rely on frequency shifting to control the solar panels during an outage, which can sometimes cause lights to flicker or the solar to turn off if the battery is full. DC coupling modulates charge smoother."
