                    "question": "Enphase Envoy",
                    "answer": "1.  Press the \"AP Mode\" button (black button) on the Envoy.\n2.  Connect your phone to the \"Envoy_XXXX\" WiFi network.\n3.  Open the **Enphase Installer Toolkit** app (you can download it as a homeowner).\n4.  It will connect and say \"Firmware Update Available.\" Tap **Update Now**.\n\n## Related Articles\n*   **[How to Monitor Battery Health](/how-to/how-to-monitor-solar-battery-health)**\n*   **[Cost of Solar Battery Replacement](/cost/solar-battery-cost-calculator-2026)**\n*   **[Best Batteries for 2026](/comparisons/best-solar-batteries-2026)**\n\n## Still Stuck?\n\nIf a power cycle didn't fix it, you likely have a hardware fault. Before calling a tech, verify the warranty status.\n\n[**How to Check Warranty Status →**](/how-to/how-to-monitor-solar-battery-health)"
